A quick fix for this customer,

Please take a backup of the SPAC db and execute the following queries on this same db and save the changes,



UPDATE ActivitySiteCollections SET URL = CONCAT('https://medpace-my.sharepoint.com/personal/' , SUBSTR(URL,11,INSTR(SUBSTR(URL,11,LENGTH(URL)),'/')-1)) WHERE URL LIKE '/personal/%';

UPDATE ActivitySiteCollections SET URL = CONCAT('https://medpace.sharepoint.com/sites/' , SUBSTR(URL,8,INSTR(SUBSTR(URL,8,LENGTH(URL)),'/')-1)) WHERE URL LIKE '/sites/%';

UPDATE ActivitySiteCollections SET URL = CONCAT('https://medpace.sharepoint.com/teams/' , SUBSTR(URL,8,INSTR(SUBSTR(URL,8,LENGTH(URL)),'/')-1)) WHERE URL LIKE '/teams/%';--- CODE ---


The above script will append the base URLs to the problematic URIs to fix the problem.

Then execute the following query on the same SPAA db,


SELECT * FROM ActivitySiteCollections WHERE URL NOT LIKE 'http%';
--- CODE ---

Please execute the SPAC System Scan job that was previously failing if the above query returns 0 records.


@Chris Brooks @Helen Randall

